channel.title: CVE Feed for Jenkins project -- Jenkins Google Kubernetes Engine Plugin
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Jenkins project -- Jenkins Google Kubernetes Engine Plugin

item.title: CVE-2020-2121|2024-08-04T07:01:40.793Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20google%20kubernetes%20engine%20plugin
item.description: Jenkins Google Kubernetes Engine Plugin 0.8.0 and earlier does not configure its YAML parser to prevent the instantiation of arbitrary types, resulting in a remote code execution vulnerability.

item.title: CVE-2019-10365|2024-08-04T22:17:20.488Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20google%20kubernetes%20engine%20plugin
item.description: Jenkins Google Kubernetes Engine Plugin 0.6.2 and earlier created a temporary file containing a temporary access token in the project workspace, where it could be accessed by users with Job/Read permission.

item.title: CVE-2019-10445|2024-08-04T22:24:18.540Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20google%20kubernetes%20engine%20plugin
item.description: A missing permission check in Jenkins Google Kubernetes Engine Plugin 0.7.0 and earlier allowed attackers with Overall/Read permission to obtain limited information about the scope of a credential with an attacker-specified credentials ID.
